## System

This instance runs on the **agentic-framework** — see `docs/concepts/three-layer-model.md` if installed.

### Layout

| Directory      | Purpose |
|----------------|---------|
| `projects/`    | Bounded work units with start/end states |
| `workstations/`| Recurring capability environments (mount any project here) |
| `services/`    | Long-running app code this instance operates |
| `expertise/`   | Curated knowledge, organized by domain |
| `working/`     | Inbox, plans, active tasks, archive |
| `system/`      | Proposals queue, toggles, registries |
| `.claude/`     | Framework agents, commands, skills |
| `hooks/`       | Event-driven automation |
| `scripts/`     | Mount, unmount, status, inventory |

### Key commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `/equip <task>` | Analyze gaps, build missing skills/agents/commands/hooks |
| `/init-project <domain>/<name>` | Start a new bounded work unit |
| `/init-workstation <name>` | Start a new capability environment |
| `/init-service <name>` | Catalog a long-running service |
| `/init-domain <path>` | Initialize a knowledge domain with curator agent |
| `/mount <project> <workstation>` | Symlink project into workstation |
| `/unmount <workstation>` | Remove mount |
| `/promote [<id>]` | Review and apply autonomous-routine proposals |
| `/refresh-status` | Regenerate `SYSTEM-STATUS.md` |
| `/sync` | Git stage + commit + push |
| `/retro` | End-of-session capture |

## Session start

1. Check active work: `ls working/active/`
2. Acknowledge: `{{INSTANCE_GREETING}}` + dive in

The hooks handle context injection automatically based on where you're working.

## Working location

ALL canonical work happens inside this instance directory (`{{INSTANCE_HOME}}`). Do not write to `/tmp`, `/home`, or other locations except for genuinely temporary state.

## Source of truth

This filesystem is the source of truth. If a remote git host is configured, push there for backup and history — but the local filesystem is canonical.

For autonomous routines (Hermes, n8n, cron): never write to canonical state directly. Always to `system/proposals/`. See `core/skills/proposal-pipeline/SKILL.md`.
